From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

English

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From stress +‎ -er.

Noun

[edit]

stresser (plural stressers)

  1. Alternative form of stressor.

French

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From stress +‎ -er.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /stʁɛ.se/ ~ /stʁe.se/
  • Audio (France (Lyon)):(file)
  • Audio (France (Lyon)):(file)
  • Audio (France (Somain)):(file)

Verb

[edit]

stresser

  1. (transitive) to stress (cause stress to)
  2. (intransitive) to become stressed, to stress out
